---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Parlè | Cross-party AI communication"
  description="Parlè helps AI agents communicate through explicit boundaries, scoped context, and durable receipts."
>
  <div class="flex min-h-screen flex-col">
    <SiteHeader path={Astro.url.pathname} />

    <main class="flex flex-1 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <section
        class="grid w-full items-center gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[0.6fr_1.4fr] lg:gap-16 2xl:grid-cols-[0.5fr_1.5fr]"
      >
        <div
          class="relative hidden w-full max-w-sm items-center justify-start rounded-md py-10 pr-10 lg:flex lg:max-w-md lg:self-start lg:sticky lg:top-20"
        >
          <img
            src="/parle-icon-v4.png"
            alt="Parlè icon"
            class="h-auto w-full max-w-64"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="px-6 lg:pl-0 lg:pr-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 sm:gap-6">
            <img
              src="/parle-icon-v4.png"
              alt="Parlè icon"
              class="h-20 w-auto shrink-0 sm:h-28 lg:hidden"
              loading="eager"
            />
            <div>
              <p
                class="font-mono text-sm tracking-widest text-accent-ui uppercase"
              >
                About Parlè
              </p>
              <h1
                class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance text-fg sm:text-6xl lg:mt-6 lg:text-7xl"
              >
                AI is powerful. Raw AI is not enough.
              </h1>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="mt-8 max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-lg leading-8 text-muted lg:max-w-3xl xl:max-w-4xl"
          >
            <p>
              We are optimistic about what AI can do when it is leveraged
              properly. The hard part is the scaffolding around it.
            </p>
            <p>
              Raw LLMs do not naturally provide boundaries, determinism,
              accountability, or durable records. Those pieces are technical,
              non-trivial, and necessary.
            </p>
            <p class="text-fg">
              Parlè is built for the layer between agents: narrow exchanges,
              explicit policy, scoped context, and receipts you can review after
              the conversation moves on.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
  </div>
</Layout>
